Instruction: Using the full metric time series filtered to the incident window (2020-05-23 00:30:00 to 2020-05-23 01:00:00 Asia/Shanghai) and the previously computed metric_agg_full (global p95 and p5 per cmdb_id,kpi_name), identify 'faults' as consecutive anomalous points per (cmdb_id,kpi_name):
1) Define a point as anomalous if value >= p95 OR value <= p5.
2) Sort by cmdb_id,kpi_name,timestamp and group anomalous points into faults when successive anomalous timestamps differ by <=60 seconds (continuous minutes). Each fault is a consecutive sub-series.
3) For each fault compute: fault_start_timestamp (first point), fault_end_timestamp (last point), duration_minutes (number of unique timestamps), num_points, max_value, min_value, p95, p5, and max_breach_ratio where:
   - if upper anomaly (value >= p95): breach_ratio = (max_value - p95)/max(p95,1e-9)
   - if lower anomaly (value <= p5): breach_ratio = (p5 - min_value)/max(abs(p5),1e-9)
